observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:
The Municipal Accountant immediately transfer the unexpended/unobligated balance of CY 2018 QRF and DRRMF-MOOE to the Trust Fund Books for easy monitoring of the utilization and to ensure the availability of this fund to support disaster risk reduction and management activities;
The Municipal Disaster and Risk Reduction Management Council consider in the formulation of disaster risk reduction management programs/projects/activities on the previous year's unexpended balance of LDRRMF to attain maximum utilization of the fund;
The LGU reverts back the CY 2010, 2011 and 2012 unutilized LDRRMF to the General Fund for other social services of the Municipality; and
The Municipal Accountant appropriately disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the LDRRMF’s amount available and utilized during the year.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, thru the Municipal Planning and Development Office ensure that the Municipality’s Annual Investment Plan will contain the detailed breakdown by clearly specifying each PPAs to be prioritized for implementation and facilitate its inclusion in the Annual Budget.
The Municipal Planning and Development Office closely monitor and evaluate the implementation of the different development programs, projects, and activities in accordance with the approved development plan;
The Municipal Mayor direct the Offices concerned to expedite the implementation of all projects funded by 20% DF to ensure optimum utilization of the fund.
